  "prompt": "How do you clean a penny board?",
  "response": "To clean a Penny board, follow these steps:\n\n1. Basic Cleaning:\n- Use a soft cloth or paper towel to wipe down the board\n- Remove loose dirt and debris\n- Use mild soap and water for stubborn dirt\n\n2. Detailed Cleaning:\n- Remove trucks and wheels for thorough cleaning\n- Clean deck with warm water and mild soap\n- Use a soft brush or cloth to scrub gently\n- Avoid soaking the board or using harsh chemicals\n- Dry completely with a clean towel\n\n3. Cleaning Trucks and Wheels:\n- Wipe down metal trucks with a damp cloth\n- Clean wheels with soap and water\n- Dry thoroughly to prevent rust\n\n4. Maintenance Tips:\n- Clean board regularly to prevent dirt buildup\n- Store in a dry place\n- Avoid extreme temperatures\n- Check for any loose parts or damage during cleaning\n\n5. What to Avoid:\n- Pressure washers\n- Abrasive cleaners\n- Leaving board wet\n- Submerging board in water\n\n6. Optional:\n- Use skateboard-specific cleaning products\n- Apply light lubricant to trucks if needed\n\nAlways let the board dry completely before reassembling and riding.",
